<dl id="s14025i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14025i">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s14all.htm#s14025i">sector 25(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> to buy a colour <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="s14025i"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/lexp.htm#s14025i">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p86.htm#s14025i">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p86.htm#s14025i">1986 (14.654)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/l22p.htm#s14025i">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#s14025i">MS V.A.17-1</ms> </li><li>JJA 14:099 </li><li><a name="p12d" href="../udra/u14da.htm#p12d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/p/p12d.htm#s14025i">Draft: 14.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">In the next place, I remembered that I had almost 100<i>l</i>. in money in London, and if it should have been asked all the soldiers in the regiment, which of them would go to Flanders, a private centinel, if they had 100<i>l</i>. in their pockets, I believe none of them would answer in the affirmative; a 100<i>l</i>. being at that time sufficient <i>to buy colours</i> in any new regiment, though not in that regiment, which was on an old establishment. <small> Daniel Defoe, <a name="DDLA" href="/udra/udex.htm#DDLA"><cite title="source">Colonel Jack</cite></a> (1908), 356</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
